      • setRegion

        public void setRegion(String region)
        Sets the AWS regions for metrics publishing.

        This parameter is optional and if not specified then metrics will be published to the region of a EC2 instance that runs this Hekate node (see EC2MetadataUtils.getEC2InstanceRegion()). If region can't be detected via EC2MetadataUtils.getEC2InstanceRegion() then AWS SDK's default region will be used.

        Parameters:
        region - AWS region.

      • setPublishInterval

        public void setPublishInterval(int publishInterval)
        Sets the time interval in seconds for pushing metrics to AWS CloudWatch.

        Note that the value of this parameter can be larger than the value metrics refresh interval as all metrics are aggregated as StatisticSets.

        Default value of this parameter is DEFAULT_PUBLISH_INTERVAL.

        Parameters:
        publishInterval - Time interval in seconds.
